{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879161302,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5a41ffeBoCGbUw7G3PWEQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa585ba00160TUuVJWlsrDOJ","messageID":"msg_d7aa4b162001X2f2vPK63kXGWV","sessionID":"ses_2855b5a41ffeBoCGbUw7G3PWEQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0e2f1515205447ea940ec6a6261ed8c1","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec — AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Requirement: Client initialization with session reuse\n\n### Scenario: Reuse existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL skip `create_session` call and use the provided `session_id` for data plane requests\n\n### Scenario: Create new session when session_id not provided\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` and valid `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are configured\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, ttl)` and store the returned `session_id`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Environment variable resolution for URLs\n\n### Scenario: Router URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` argument is `None` and environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to the value of `ROUTER_URL`\n\n### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` argument is `None` and environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be set to the value of `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Authentication token resolution\n\n### Scenario: Token from explicit argument\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is provided to `ControlPlaneClient.__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the session SHALL include `Authorization: Bearer {auth_token}` header\n\n### Scenario: Token from service account file\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** the token SHALL be read via `read_token_from_file` and set as `Authorization` header\n\n### Scenario: No token available\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and service account token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** no `Authorization` header SHALL be set\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Context manager protocol\n\n### Scenario: Context manager enters and returns self\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL initialize data plane (if not already) and return `self`\n\n### Scenario: Context manager exit calls stop\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as context manager\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called (with any exception tuple or None)\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `stop()` and return `False`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session cleanup on stop\n\n### Scenario: Stop deletes session when session_id was created\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was created by the client (not passed in)\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(session_id)` and close the data plane client\n\n### Scenario: Stop does not delete session when session_id was provided\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was passed to `__init__` (reused session)\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL close the data plane client but NOT call `delete_session`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Execute command with timeout handling\n\n### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")` is called with `timeout=None`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent to `api/execute`\n- **THEN** the timeout string SHALL be `\"120s\"` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\", timeout=30)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout string SHALL be `\"30s\"` and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds\n\n### Scenario: Execute command with non-zero exit raises error\n- **GIVEN** the server returns JSON `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error message\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error message\", command=command)`\n\n### Scenario: Execute command with zero exit returns stdout\n- **GIVEN** the server returns JSON `{\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\", \"stderr\": \"\"}`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"output\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Run code with language mapping\n\n### Scenario: Run Python code\n- **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the code is executed\n- **THEN** a timestamped `.py` file SHALL be written via `write_file` and `python3 <file>` SHALL be executed via `execute_command`\n\n### Scenario: Run Python3 variant language\n- **GIVEN** `language` is `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n- **WHEN** `run_code` processes the language\n- **THEN** it SHALL be treated as Python and write a `.py` file\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: File operations\n\n### Scenario: Write file with base64 encoding\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello world\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent to `api/files`\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON with `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n### Scenario: Upload file as multipart\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/path.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent to `api/files`\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a multipart POST with `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`\n\n### Scenario: Download file\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/file.txt\", \"/local/file.txt\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files/remote/file.txt` with `stream=True` and write chunks to local path\n\n### Scenario: List files\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/workspace\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files?path=/workspace` and return the parsed JSON response\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Data plane URL construction\n\n### Scenario: Base URL from router_url\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"` and `namespace=\"prod\"` and `cr_name=\"my-interpreter\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` constructs `self.base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `\"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n\n### Scenario: Base URL provided explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"http://custom.example.com/api/\"` is passed\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://custom.example.com/api/\"` regardless of `router_url`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session header propagation\n\n### Scenario: x-agentcube-session-id header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"abc123\"`\n- **WHEN** any `_request` is called\n- **THEN** the headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: abc123`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Error handling for data plane init failure\n\n### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session creation\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was created by the client and `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the exception\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Default values\n\n### Scenario: Default constructor values\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n### Scenario: Default HTTP session pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` or `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775879161290,"end":1775879161298}}}}
