{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879167514,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5a41ffeBoCGbUw7G3PWEQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa59df8001N2HWsAKgXkV75i","messageID":"msg_d7aa592a8001OZ9WUfd403GEfr","sessionID":"ses_2855b5a41ffeBoCGbUw7G3PWEQ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f7af1f41f8fa435b8780645161825a6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: AR: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Purpose\n11: \n12: Implement K8s/AgentCube provider integration for deploying AI agents as either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime CR), enabling lifecycle management through CLI commands.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Requirements\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider initialization\n19: \n20: The system SHALL construct `KubernetesProvider` with configurable namespace, kubeconfig path, and verbose logging.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Default namespace and kubeconfig\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider` is instantiated without arguments\n25: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n26: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` SHALL default to `None` (using in-cluster or default kubeconfig), and `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Custom kubeconfig path\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a custom kubeconfig file path is provided\n31: - **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.__init__(kubeconfig=\"/path/to/config\")` runs\n32: - **THEN** the client SHALL load configuration from the specified file via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: Namespace auto-creation\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** the specified namespace does not exist in the cluster\n37: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` is called\n38: - **THEN** the provider SHALL create the namespace with `kubernetes.client.V1Namespace(metadata=V1ObjectMeta(name=namespace))` and log the creation\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — deploy agent\n43: \n44: The system SHALL create or patch a `Deployment` and a `NodePort` `Service` for the agent, returning deployment info.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Deployment creation\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** `deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, replicas=1, node_port=None, env_vars=None)` is called\n49: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n50: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n51:   - Call `_create_deployment` with sanitized name (DNS-compliant: lowercase, alphanumeric, hyphens, max 63 chars)\n52:   - Call `_create_service` with the same sanitized name\n53:   - Ensure namespace exists via `_ensure_namespace`\n54:   - Return dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: NodePort assignment\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is specified in range 30000-32767\n59: - **WHEN** `_create_service` creates the Service\n60: - **THEN** the Service spec SHALL set `type: NodePort` with `nodePort: {node_port}` and `port: {port}` targeting the container port\n61: - **AND** `service_url` SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Auto NodePort\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `node_port` is `None`\n66: - **WHEN** the Service is created\n67: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL assign a random NodePort in the valid range\n68: - **AND** the provider SHALL retrieve the assigned port from the Service status\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Entrypoint override\n71: \n72: - **GIVEN** `entrypoint` is provided\n73: - **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n74: - **THEN** `command` SHALL be set to the entrypoint command (parsed as list if string)\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Environment variables injection\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `env_vars` dict is provided\n79: - **WHEN** the Deployment container spec is constructed\n80: - **THEN** each key-value pair SHALL be added as `V1EnvVar(name=key, value=value)`\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Sanitize name\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** an agent name with special characters or uppercase\n85: - **WHEN** `_sanitize_name(name)` runs\n86: - **THEN** the result SHALL be: lowercase, replace underscores and spaces with hyphens, strip non-alphanumeric/hyphen chars, truncate to 63 chars, strip leading/trailing hyphens\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — wait for deployment ready\n91: \n92: The system SHALL poll deployment status until all replicas are ready or timeout.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Successful rollout\n95: \n96: - **GIVEN** a Deployment with `replicas=3`\n97: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` is called\n98: - **THEN** the provider SHALL poll `read_namespaced_deployment_status` until `status.ready_replicas == replicas` and log progress\n99: - **AND** return when ready within timeout\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Timeout failure\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** deployment pods fail to become ready\n104: - **WHEN** `timeout` seconds elapse without all replicas ready\n105: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout} seconds\")`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — get agent status\n110: \n111: The system SHALL retrieve deployment and service status for the agent.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Status retrieval\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** an agent was deployed via `deploy_agent`\n116: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status(agent_name)` is called\n117: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n118:   - Read Deployment status (name, namespace, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas)\n119:   - Read Service status (name, port, node_port)\n120:   - Return dict with `status` (`\"running\"` if ready, `\"pending\"` if not ready, `\"not_found\"` if missing)\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Deployment not found\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** no Deployment exists for `agent_name`\n125: - **WHEN** `get_agent_status` is called\n126: - **THEN** Kubernetes API SHALL raise `kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException` with status 404\n127: - **AND** the provider SHALL catch it and return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: KubernetesProvider — delete agent\n132: \n133: The system SHALL delete Deployment and Service resources.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Successful deletion\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a deployed agent\n138: - **WHEN** `delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n139: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n140:   - Delete Deployment with `delete_namespaced_deployment`\n141:   - Delete Service with `delete_namespaced_service`\n142:   - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Ignore 404 on deletion\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** one or both resources do not exist\n147: - **WHEN** deletion API returns 404\n148: - **THEN** the provider SHALL ignore the error (treat as already deleted) and continue\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider initialization\n153: \n154: The system SHALL construct `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR operations.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Default configuration\n157: \n158: - **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated\n159: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n160: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `kubeconfig` to `None`, `verbose` to `False`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Custom namespace\n163: \n164: - **GIVEN** a specific namespace is required\n165: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"custom-ns\")` is instantiated\n166: - **THEN** all CR operations SHALL target that namespace\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — deploy AgentRuntime CR\n171: \n172: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom resource in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: CR creation\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** `deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint=None, env_vars=None, workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, readiness_probe_path=None, readiness_probe_port=None)` is called\n177: - **WHEN** the CR is applied\n178: - **THEN** the provider SHALL:\n179:   - Sanitize agent name via `_sanitize_name`\n180:   - Ensure namespace exists\n181:   - Construct CR body with:\n182:     - `apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n183:     - `kind: AgentRuntime`\n184:     - `metadata.name`, `metadata.namespace`\n185:     - `spec.image`, `spec.port`\n186:     - `spec.command` if entrypoint provided\n187:     - `spec.env` from env_vars (plus `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL` if not in env_vars)\n188:     - `spec.sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `spec.maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n189:     - `spec.imagePullSecrets: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n190:     - `spec.readinessProbe` if probe path/port provided\n191:   - Create via CustomObjectsApi `create_namespaced_custom_object`\n192:   - Return dict with `cr_name`, `namespace`, `status`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL injection\n195: \n196: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n197: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n198: - **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Router URL injection\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided and not in `env_vars`\n203: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n204: - **THEN** `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be added to `spec.env`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n207: \n208: - **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` are provided\n209: - **WHEN** the CR spec is constructed\n210: - **THEN** `spec.readinessProbe` SHALL include:\n211:   - `httpGet.path: {readiness_probe_path}`\n212:   - `httpGet.port: {readiness_probe_port}`\n213:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n214:   - `periodSeconds: 10`\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: AgentCubeProvider — get AgentRuntime CR\n219: \n220: The system SHALL retrieve the AgentRuntime CR and its status.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: CR retrieval\n223: \n224: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists\n225: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime(name, namespace)` is called\n226: - **THEN** the provider SHALL use `get_namespaced_custom_object` with:\n227:   - `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n228:   - `version=\"v1alpha1\"`\n229:   - `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n230:   - `namespace`, `name`\n231:   - Return the full CR dict or `None` if not found\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: CR not found\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime CR exists for the name\n236: - **WHEN** `get_agent_runtime` is called\n237: - **THEN** the API SHALL raise 404\n238: - **AND** the provider SHALL catch and return `None`\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: CLI publish — provider selection\n243: \n244: The system SHALL route publish operations to `AgentCubeProvider` or `KubernetesProvider` based on `--provider` option.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider publish\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` is specified\n249: - **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n250: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n251:   - Validate `metadata.router_url` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` are set (raise `ValueError` if missing)\n252:   - Call `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime`\n253:   - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"AgentRuntime\", \"cr_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ...}`\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: K8s provider publish\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--provider k8s` is specified\n258: - **WHEN** `publish` command runs\n259: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n260:   - Call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`\n261:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)`\n262:   - Update metadata with `k8s_deployment: {\"type\": \"Deployment\", \"deployment_name\": ..., \"service_name\": ..., \"namespace\": ..., \"node_port\": ...}`\n263:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on readiness timeout, recording error in metadata\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Provider default\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** `--provider` is omitted\n268: - **WHEN** `publish` runs\n269: - **THEN** `provider` SHALL default to `\"agentcube\"`\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ### Requirement: CLI invoke — provider-aware endpoint resolution\n274: \n275: The system SHALL resolve invocation endpoint based on deployment type in metadata.\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime invocation URL\n278: \n279: - **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n280: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n281: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be constructed as:\n282:   - `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: K8s Deployment invocation URL\n285: \n286: - **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n287: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n288: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `http://localhost:{node_port}` from `k8s_deployment.node_port`\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Direct HTTP invocation for K8s\n291: \n292: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and endpoint is a direct HTTP URL\n293: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` runs\n294: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL `POST` JSON payload to the endpoint with custom headers\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: CLI status — provider-aware status retrieval\n299: \n300: The system SHALL retrieve status based on deployment type.\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR status\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"agentcube\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n305: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n306: - **THEN** status SHALL be:\n307:   - `cr_object[\"status\"][\"status\"]` if present\n308:   - `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\", \"agentEndpoint\": cr[\"status\"][\"agentEndpoint\"]}` if CR exists but status field missing\n309:   - `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` if CR does not exist\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: K8s Deployment status\n312: \n313: - **GIVEN** `provider=\"k8s\"` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"Deployment\"`\n314: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n315: - **THEN** status SHALL come from `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status`\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Not published status\n318: \n319: - **GIVEN** `metadata.agent_id` is `None`\n320: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` runs\n321: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ### Requirement: CLI status — exit codes\n326: \n327: The system SHALL exit with code 1 for non-ready states.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Not published exit\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** status is `\"not_published\"`\n332: - **WHEN** `status` command prints output\n333: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print guidance message and exit with code `1`\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Error status exit\n336: \n337: - **GIVEN** status is `\"error\"`\n338: - **WHEN** `status` command completes\n339: - **THEN** CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: Session header consistency\n344: \n345: The system SHALL use consistent session header naming across providers and SDK.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Invoke session header\n348: \n349: - **GIVEN** `metadata.session_id` exists\n350: - **WHEN** HTTP invocation is performed\n351: - **THEN** request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (uppercase X, capitalized Session, Id)\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Header response handling\n354: \n355: - **GIVEN** a response contains session header\n356: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n357: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL read `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) from response headers\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ### Requirement: Error handling for provider operations\n362: \n363: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API exceptions gracefully.\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: API exception in verbose mode\n366: \n367: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API exception occurs and `verbose=True`\n368: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n369: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print `Error {command}: {exception}` in red and full traceback, then exit with code `1`\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Missing Kubernetes dependency\n372: \n373: - **GIVEN** `kubernetes` package is not installed\n374: - **WHEN** provider classes are imported\n375: - **THEN** import SHALL fail or be caught, and CLI SHALL print message suggesting `pip install agentcube[k8s]`\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Implementation Files\n380: \n381: | File | Purpose |\n382: |------|---------|\n383: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n384: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n385: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s`, `_publish_cr_to_k8s` |\n386: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube`, `_direct_http_invocation` |\n387: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status`, `_get_cr_k8s_status` |\n388: \n389: ---\n390: \n391: ## Dependencies\n392: \n393: | Package | Purpose |\n394: |---------|---------|\n395: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s API client, CustomObjectsApi |\n396: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invocation |\n397: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model |\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## Validation Checklist\n402: \n403: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n404: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace` creates namespace if missing\n405: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n406: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name` produces DNS-compliant names\n407: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` polls with timeout\n408: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` returns running/pending/not_found\n409: - [ ] `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` removes resources, ignores 404\n410: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.__init__` with namespace, kubeconfig, verbose params\n411: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` creates AgentRuntime CR\n412: - [ ] `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` retrieves CR or returns None\n413: - [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s` uses KubernetesProvider\n414: - [ ] `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s` uses AgentCubeProvider\n415: - [ ] `InvokeRuntime` resolves endpoint based on k8s_deployment.type\n416: - [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` for Deployment type\n417: - [ ] `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` for AgentRuntime type\n418: - [ ] CLI status exits with code 1 for not_published/error\n\n(End of file - total 418 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\nAR: AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement K8s/AgentCube provider integration for deploying AI agents as either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime CR), enabling lifecycle management through CLI commands.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: KubernetesProvider initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `KubernetesProvider` with configurable namespace, kubeconfig path, and verbose logging.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879167505,"end":1775879167511}}}}
